  "prompt": "How can I contact payment and settlement department of RBI?",
  "response": "To contact the Payment and Settlement Department of the Reserve Bank of India (RBI), you can use the following methods:\n\n1. Official Website:\n- Visit www.rbi.org.in\n- Navigate to \"Contact Us\" section\n\n2. Postal Address:\nPayment and Settlement Systems Department\nReserve Bank of India\nCentral Office\nMumbai - 400 001\n\n3. Phone Numbers:\n- RBI Central Office Switchboard: 022-2260 1000\n- General Helpline: 1800 345 1766\n\n4. Email:\n- For general queries: helpdoc@rbi.org.in\n- For specific department: dpss@rbi.org.in\n\n5. Direct Contact:\nYou may contact the specific department through their official communication channels mentioned on the RBI website.\n\nImportant Tips:\n- Check the official RBI website for the most updated contact information\n- Prepare your specific query or concern before contacting\n- Have relevant documentation ready\n- Be clear and concise in your communication\n\nNote: Contact details may change, so it's always best to verify the current information from the official RBI website.",
